               <p>WILLIAM SNELL. I am <rs id="t18250915-243-viclabel1300" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-243-victim1250 t18250915-243-viclabel1300"></join> to Mr. Cook, of <placeName id="t18250915-243-crimeloc1301">Hyde Park-corner</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-243-crimeloc1301" type="placeName" value="Hyde Park-corner"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-243-crimeloc1301" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-243-off1298 t18250915-243-crimeloc1301"></join>. The prisoner was my fellow <rs id="t18250915-243-deflabel1302" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-243-defend1249 t18250915-243-deflabel1302"></join>. On the 18th of July, I got up in the morning, and found my pocket-book by the side of my box, which had been in the box the night before. The box was locked and the key in my breeches' pocket; I asked the prisoner about it, and he said the key was down the privy - that he had taken 6 d. from the book, and he hoped I would forgive him. I then missed my watch from my box - he said "I beg your pardon, I will go and fetch the watch;" which he did.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-243-person1251">
                  JAMES 
                  COOK
               <interp inst="t18250915-243-person1251" type="surname" value="COOK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-243-person1251" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-243-person1251" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am Park-keeper. The prosecutor is my servant; he told me he had lost his watch, and the prisoner must have it; I called the prisoner and told him it would be worse for him if he did not tell where it was; he then went into the cellar and fetched it out of the sand.</p>
               <p>
